Someone executed a (additional) diagnostic action on the system. The action (type, target_component, description, outcome) was: 
TYPE: Test,
TARGET: ambient sensor (control) module relay path and PCB traces,
DESCRIPTION: With power removed, use a continuity / low‑ohms measurement from the control module input + terminal to the relay common contact, from the relay common to the relay NO contact, and from the relay NO contact to the control module output + terminal. Then visually inspect and probe for any unintended series resistor, wrong track, or miswired jumpers that might be inserted between relay output and the output terminal. Note where continuity is lost or where unexpected resistance (more than a fraction of an ohm) appears in series with the relay output path.,
RESULT: Continuity from Control Input Cable (+) through the Control Relay to Control Output Cable (+) measures as a short (0.01–0.10 Ω) with no unexpected series resistance detected. The Control Relay connections are: port p → Control Input Cable (+), port n → Control Output Cable (+). The Control Output Cable (+) is continuous to the Load Input Cable (+) with no additional components indicated in series.
